Would it be possible to prevent users from entering HTML in their Full Name?  Perhaps by just not allowing either of the the < or the > characters.

Although JIRA itself seems to handle this properly, plugins don't always handle it correctly.  I've found the issue in both the [JIRA Voters and Watchers plugin|https://studio.plugins.atlassian.com/browse/VOTE-31] and and old version of the [JIRA Timesheet Plugin|https://studio.plugins.atlassian.com/browse/TIME-13].

I know there are lots of places plugin makers could introduce security holes, but I think this one might as well be closed at the source since it's really not much of a benefit for users to be able to put <>'s in their name.

